description: Ad Fontes Media is a Public Benefit Corporation that rates the news. It was founded by Vanessa Otero, creator of the Media Bias Chart®.
industries: E-Learning, EdTech, Higher Education, Journalism, Media and Entertainment, News, Social Entrepreneurship, Social Impact, Software
industry_groups: Community and Lifestyle, Content and Publishing, Education, Media and Entertainment, Other, Software
full_description:
Ad Fontes Media, Inc. is a company founded in 2018 by Vanessa Otero, creator of the Media Bias Chart®. The mission of Ad Fontes Media is “to make news consumers smarter and news media better.”

Ad Fontes rates the news for reliability and bias to help people navigate the news landscape. Ad Fontes is Latin for “to the source,” because at the heart of what Ad Fontes Media does is look at the source—analyze the very content itself—to rate it. Ad Fontes has created a system of news content ratings that has beneficial applications for all stakeholders in a healthy news media landscape, including consumers, educators, journalism outlets, researchers, advertisers, and social media platforms. Ad Fontes currently creates ratings with a small team of human analysts who have political views from across the spectrum. The analysts are trained to look at the content of the news and score it according to a consistent methodology. Ad Fontes provides the news source ratings themselves as a reference product for consumers and educators—mainly through through its widely known Media Bias Chart. Ad Fontes also now offers a software platform for educators to teach students how to rate the news using its approach.


Ad Fontes Media is incorporated as a Public Benefit Corporation (PBC) in Colorado. The stated public benefit of Ad Fontes Media is the same as its mission. It is currently funded by its founder, by a crowdfunding campaign which ran in late 2018,  by sales of licenses, prints, data products, and educational products, and by donations (non-tax-deductible) by individuals who believe in its mission.

description: Agoric provides a framework for programming smart contracts securely and with ease, beyond anything available today.
industries: Blockchain, Cryptocurrency, Developer Platform, E-Commerce Platforms, Software
industry_groups: Commerce and Shopping, Financial Services, Internet Services, Other, Payments, Software
full_description:
Agoric is a framework that provides security and ease in programming smart contracts, beyond anything available today. Agoric’s mission is to provide a secure smart contracts framework to the entire blockchain ecosystem. With Agoric, which makes it easier to build and deploy smart contracts in JavaScript, millions of programmers worldwide will have safer, simpler tools to build smart contracts and applications. In addition, composability enables rapid development and competitive advantage. With secure smart contracts, we envision unprecedented, widespread forms of global cooperation, and entrepreneurs creating fundamentally new businesses enabled by digital assets. Agoric is here to make that opportunity a reality.

The Agoric team includes world-class technologists, economists, business leaders and community builders on a quest to bring smart contracts into the future. Members of the Agoric team have been professional collaborators in smart contracts technology for over 30 years, and have now reunited to enact this mission. Agoric has collaborated with Cosmos and other well-known projects, and is backed by Outlier Ventures, Kilowatt Capital, gumi Cryptos Capital, MetaStable Capital, Lemniscap, Xpring, Rockaway Blockchain and the Interchain Foundation, as well as additional funding from Naval Ravikant and Polychain.

description: Delivering peace of mind, by replacing traditional networking with software defined security solutions.
industries: Cloud Infrastructure, Cyber Security, IT Infrastructure, Network Security, Software Engineering
industry_groups: Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Privacy and Security, Science and Engineering, Software
full_description:
Arroyo delivers software-driven network security, allowing IT professionals to enhance their traditional networks with solutions capable of withstanding the challenges of today’s cyber-security landscape. 

Introducing INFLOW by Arroyo. INFLOW elminates the need to purchase expensive, slow, and outdated networking appliances and virtual machines. INFLOW is a Networking-as-a-Service Platform which been built from the ground up, leveraging recent advances in Cloud-Native Network Functions (CNFs). Customers can subscribe to and use INFLOW to increase their network security, either in the cloud or on-premise, by extending their edge and applying advanced network functions. Networks can be upgraded with next-generation firewalls, intrusion detection and prevention, phishing protection, user VPNs, load-balancing and much more. All available at the click of a button and without hardware and VMs.

With no systems to install or manage, no firmware to update, no rules to keep in sync: INFLOW lowers administrative overhead while offering heightened security. No Hardware, No Firmware: Just Security.

This process guarantees we’ll be successful in presenting you with at least 2 exceptional candidates (or 1 that you hire) within 30 days, no matter the complexity of your requirement.

Visit us at www.BearhugRecruiting.com to learn more and review our recent case studies.

full_description:

BentoML is an open-source platform for high-performance machine learning model serving. It makes it easy to build production API endpoint for your ML model and supports all major machine learning frameworks, including Tensorflow, Keras, PyTorch, XGBoost, scikit-learn, fastai and more.

BentoML comes with a high-performance API model server with adaptive micro-batching support, bringing the advantage of batch processing to online serving workloads. It also provides batch serving, model management and model deployment functionality, which gives ML teams an end-to-end model serving solution, with DevOps best practices baked in.

description: The Blockchain Art Collective provides unparalleled provenance tracking to artists, collectors, dealers, and institutions.
industries: Art, Blockchain, Internet of Things, Security, Software
industry_groups: Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Other, Privacy and Security, Software
full_description:
The Blockchain Art Collective provides unparalleled provenance tracking to artists, collectors, dealers, and institutions. It assigns security to a physical work of art, which stays connected to it over time. This identity, or Blockchain Art Certificate of Authenticity (COA), is created digitally and physically using Blockchain and Internet of Things (IoT) technology. Some key benefits of using these COAs include creating a holistic and secure provenance record, tracking transport of artworks and title transfers, and preventing counterfeit art. 

Its platform is powered by Chronicled, Inc., a technology company founded in 2014 to leverage blockchain and IoT to power smart, secure supply chain solutions. The company has developed a decentralized protocol and network for supply chain to enforce cross-organization business rules without revealing private data. 

For more information, visit the company at: blockchainartcollective.com
For general art and blockchain education follow its blog at: medium.com/ethereum-art-collective

full_description:
Bonafi is a Blockchain company based in Los Angeles. Our team is dedicated in solving the problem of counterfeit products plaguing the world. Each one of us here at Bonafi has been a victim to counterfeit goods, and we are personally invested in eradicating it from our society.

and quickly deploy new features to meet client demands. The

estate industry and into new verticals.

description: It's an all-in-one platform
industries: CRM, Home Services, Marketplace, Mobile Apps, Real Estate, SaaS, Service Industry, Software
industry_groups: Apps, Commerce and Shopping, Information Technology, Mobile, Other, Real Estate, Sales and Marketing, Software
full_description:
ChoreRelief provides a transparent, competitive marketplace for consumers to manage home repairs. The app connects consumers with contractors and home improvement professionals in order to create a worry-free experience.

ChoreRelief combines the main elements of both networks and marketplaces. We use SaaS workflow software to focus action around longer-term projects, not just a quick transaction. The tool lets repair and maintenance professionals perform critical tasks, send bids, and collect payments, etc. It promotes these service providers as differentiated individuals, helping build long-term relationships with clients.

It also permits property managers, landlords, and homeowners with an opportunity to post their repair and maintenance needs, and optionally, the budget within which they’re working. This streamlines the match-making process for both parties.

Customers and providers are each unique; they are not interchangeable commodities as with Lyft or Uber. Each person brings unique expertise, needs, and viewpoints to the transaction and the relationship. Our market network is designed to acknowledge that as a core tenet and provide solutions that accommodate it. The company’s mission is to expand globally while seamlessly connecting property owners with contractors. The result is more accessible talent, affordable rates, a single source for the endless needs of property owners, and more business for contractors.

We view ourselves as innovators and collaborators, not competitors. That’s why we do our best to build networks that promote collaboration among contractors. It’s the underlying focus of everything we do because we want to solve problems for everyone using technology who wants to join us and make history.

full_description:
Surgeries are complicated and ORs are some of the most expensive real estate in the world. Challenges come from all angles - from delayed start-times resulting in domino delays and overlapping cases to staff struggling to navigate complex, disconnected legacy systems, little frictions can lead to major ripples resulting in inefficiencies and unfavorable outcomes for providers and patients. 

At ConnectOR, we've developed a suite of simple, integrated solutions that solve critical pain-points across the surgical journey. We start with our interconnected scheduling portal and team messaging modules that seamlessly push critical data to our surgical coordination platform for teams to stay informed and in sync. From informing patient families with automated, real-time procedure updates to empowering OR managers with valuable metrics on what matters most to your team, our intuitive modular platform and a forward-thinking product pipeline addresses challenges across your surgical workflow - creating value and reducing frictions for all our users from caregivers to administrators.

The future of surgery is Connected.

description: Coral is a human-centric robotics company, designing robots for people to enhance their everyday lives.
industries: Artificial Intelligence, Consumer Electronics, Electronics, Product Design, Robotics, UX Design
industry_groups: Artificial Intelligence, Consumer Electronics, Data and Analytics, Design, Hardware, Science and Engineering, Software
full_description:
Coral is a human-centric robotics company, designing robots for people to enhance their everyday lives. We believe that purpose-driven robots empower all people to achieve more.

Robots have always been one of the greatest dreams and fears of people. We marvel at their capabilities, yet are terrified of what they can become. We want them to be intelligent, yet are constantly disappointed. We saw this paradox and thought what can we do differently?

Using our backgrounds in engineering and design, we saw that we can use a thoughtful and people-first approach to making robots. Robots should work with people rather than do things only on their own. This relationship between person and robot should be one that’s constructive.

When we were looking at where to call Coral home, it was important to us that it be a place filled with creativity, energy, and next to the ocean. We wanted to be in a place where we can foster talent and spark innovation. We wanted to be in a place where we can be reminded of the values of our brand. More importantly, we wanted to build a community of people who use design and robotics to empower people. That’s why Los Angeles is our home.

We think robotics is an innovative and exciting space. We see a future with an ecosystem of robots that work together to help people in their daily lives. It’s important for us that we need to use thoughtful design to help get us to that future now.

description: Corsha’s API Security Platform prevents network attacks through dynamic, fully automated multi-factor authentication for APIs.
industries: Cloud Security, Cyber Security, IT Infrastructure, SaaS, Security
industry_groups: Information Technology, Privacy and Security, Software
full_description:
Corsha is a leading cybersecurity company that is defining the landscape of API security.  APIs are the glue that stitch together hybrid and multi-cloud networks. Our game-changing API Security Platform solves the growing security concerns facing enterprises as attacks on APIs increase.  Our platform empowers CTOs, CISOs and other security professionals to protect their data and applications as they traverse hybrid and multi-cloud environments.

Corsha has developed the first and only dynamic, fully automated multi-factor authentication (MFA) for APIs.  We protect APIs using the same MFA principles that have successfully protected systems from human username/password cyberattacks.

By enabling MFA for every API call, our platform cryptographically defines the network so that only authorized machines can connect to applications and data, resulting in a dynamic identity for every deployed machine.  

Through our central management console, security professionals have full visibility into and complete control of all API activity across cloud and enterprise networks.

Our platform is deployed as Corsha Cloud (SaaS) or Corsha Enterprise (self-hosted).  It integrates with modern DevOps pipelines and is cloud-native, highly scalable, and platform agnostic.

With the power of Okto, now, businesses can maximize their results and delight their customers.

description: Corsha’s API Security Platform prevents network attacks through dynamic, fully automated multi-factor authentication for APIs.
industries: Cloud Security, Cyber Security, IT Infrastructure, SaaS, Security
industry_groups: Information Technology, Privacy and Security, Software
full_description:
Corsha is a leading cybersecurity company that is defining the landscape of API security.  APIs are the glue that stitch together hybrid and multi-cloud networks. Our game-changing API Security Platform solves the growing security concerns facing enterprises as attacks on APIs increase.  Our platform empowers CTOs, CISOs and other security professionals to protect their data and applications as they traverse hybrid and multi-cloud environments.

Corsha has developed the first and only dynamic, fully automated multi-factor authentication (MFA) for APIs.  We protect APIs using the same MFA principles that have successfully protected systems from human username/password cyberattacks.

By enabling MFA for every API call, our platform cryptographically defines the network so that only authorized machines can connect to applications and data, resulting in a dynamic identity for every deployed machine.  

Through our central management console, security professionals have full visibility into and complete control of all API activity across cloud and enterprise networks.

Our platform is deployed as Corsha Cloud (SaaS) or Corsha Enterprise (self-hosted).  It integrates with modern DevOps pipelines and is cloud-native, highly scalable, and platform agnostic.

description: Crypto Key Stack is a software based hardware wallets help protect your keys while transacting.
industries: Blockchain, Consumer Goods, Cryptocurrency, Security, Software
industry_groups: Consumer Goods, Financial Services, Other, Payments, Privacy and Security, Software
full_description:
Crypto Key Stack is a software based hardware wallets help protect your keys while transacting. Crypto Key Stack LLC was co-founded by Chris Gonyo and NFL veteran Israel Idonije in an effort to reduce the billions of dollars lost due to improper private key storage. The number of assets being stored and tracked on the blockchain is growing at an exponential rate, and they are all being secured by private keys.

Realizing that software-based hardware wallets are excellent for cybersecurity,  but become vulnerable in the event of a physical disaster, Chris and Israel designed Crypto Key Stack to help preserve access to your assets in the event of a hardware failure and physical disaster. It was created out of a need for an affordable, high-quality stainless steel backup device that allowed users to store multiple cryptographic keys permanently.

description: DIRT is a protocol for decentralized information curation that uses token staking to incentivize honesty.
industry_groups: Information Technology
full_description:
DIRT is a protocol for decentralized information curation that uses token staking to incentivize honesty. DIRT is not a Token Curated Registry (TCR). DIRT is a protocol to build TCRs. 

Similar to Wikipedia, DIRT allows anyone to contribute information. DIRT maintains accuracy at scale because every contributor needs to deposit tokens to write data. If the data is correct, it is freely shared. If the data is incorrect, anyone can challenge the data and earn tokens for identifying these inaccurate facts. Their protocol and platform makes it economically irrational for misinformation to persist in a data set.

description: A blockchain app to offer any service anytime, anywhere, or conversely access and respond to demands for services.
industry_groups: Information Technology, Internet Services
full_description:
Euphrates is the exciting new universal app that allows you to offer any service (e.g. jobs, projects, tasks) anytime, anywhere, or conversely access and respond to demands for services. Whether you are in need of assistance, or one who can provide the assistance, Euphrates is a real-time, highly flexible, and user-friendly application that is perfect for the Gig Economy. Using blockchain technology, it's built for the enterprising. Move from completing a gig to growing a business. Take a look at some of the exciting new ways that Euphrates can empower you:

a. It's a bi-directional tool, roles are not restrained. Anyone can offer, or demand services. So, hire whatever service you need, and when you need it. Or, offer any service you perform. Any job, anytime, anywhere. With a single universal app, you can drop the rest. 

b. Euphrates is built on blockchain. Link automated smart contracts to facilitate transactions on the fly; extend your reach, connect with new partners and new opportunites, and grow a business, not just complete a gig.

c. Create extensions of your business naturally. The Euphrates platform allows multiple real-time natural language communications on a user-friendly screen. Text, image, and voice all in one place. Negotiate price and make payments directly from your calls. Adapt organically to market conditions as they exist. Call in backup for big jobs. 

d. We won't second-guess your needs with restrictive drop-down menus that limit your roles and gigs. We let you decide what service is best for you. Offer your services when and where you want. Your hours of operation, specific offerings, and wages are all yours to define. 

e. Employers and providers both rate one another with every job. User ratings are backed with cash - only real jobs are rated, and the system can't be gamed by buying 'likes.'​ Understand who you're working with.

industries: Artificial Intelligence, Consumer Applications, Fitness, Software
industry_groups: Apps, Artificial Intelligence, Data and Analytics, Science and Engineering, Software, Sports
full_description:
Prove Labs is an innovative startup founded in 2018 in Brooklyn, NY, focusing on using A.I. smartphone vision to better track and improve human movements for a stronger and healthier body.	 	

Prove Labs is composed of a multidisciplinary team of A.I. deep learning engineers, smartphone vision experts, and Mobile UX designers.  	

Prove Labs' first app - FitCam: Fitness Trainer - is a revolutionary workout companion, its mobile A.I. technology is tracking, recording and providing deep analysis of users' workout sessions by just using the iPhone's camera.	 	

FitCam: Fitness Trainer is the first app to provide an accurate quantitative and qualitative tracking of a fitness workout with no equipment necessary other than the iPhone. FitCam counts repetitions, evaluates your form, grades your movements and provides a score for each workout, also providing advice on how to improve your form and ultimately get more from your training. 	 	

FitCam PushUps is connected to Apple Health & Activity, and it’s a unique experience on the Apple App Store, having gained over 5k installs within the first 2 months, and an average rating of 4.5 stars.

full_description:

The company helps users take back control over private information and seamlessly authenticate in digital services. For companies, GATACA offers single-sign-on authentication tools to cut the time, manpower and cost currently needed to comply with KYC, while drastically improving the user onboarding experience.

description: Precision, real-time indoor positioning of visitors, staff and assets for game-changing insights and engagement.
industries: Analytics, Big Data, Indoor Positioning, Information Technology, Internet of Things, Retail Technology, SaaS
industry_groups: Commerce and Shopping, Data and Analytics, Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Navigation and Mapping, Software
full_description:
Xenio's true precision indoor positioning platform, fuses the physical and digital worlds. We empower physical businesses to engage with their visitors in an entirely new, individualized way. By combining IoT, RF, and precise indoor positioning technologies, the Xenio platform enables brick & mortar retail, hospitals, airports, hotels, etc.  to precisely track each visitor's real-time behavior within and connect with them in an individualized way, at the right place, and at the right time. 

This is NOT beaconing or proximity marketing but a revolutionary new way to deliver accurate indoor X-Y position of people and assets with 2 foot accuracy along with all the software features to extract value from this new data.
 
Highly contextual shopper engagement based on actual behavior has never been possible in physical stores and is akin to what online-retailers have been able to do for over a decade.
 
Xenio’s unique platform enables in-store marketing to match the level of accuracy and engagement of online marketing, optimizing the online and offline shopper journey and turning the physical store into a strategic advantage.

description: Decentralized Token Ratings

full_description:
VEVA offers decentralized, collusion-proof token ratings. We are built blockchain-first, running our entire backend—databases, analyst registry, payments, token history, etc.—via Ethereum Smart Contracts.

Our vision is to become the ratings platform for crypto.  We see crypto growing to tens of millions of tokens representing trillions of dollars.  This is finance2.0 which will include new digital assets as well as traditional financial assets.  Some core functions in finance1.0, such as ratings, will need to be re-engineered for crypto. Specifically, we'll need to solve for hyper-scale and trust.  Incumbents are incapable of making the transition.  VEVA is building the Moodys/S&P for finance2.0.

description: Blockchain, News, Platform
industry_groups: Content and Publishing, Information Technology, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment
full_description:
The Terciv blockchain platform was designed to tackle the global epidemic of fake news and purposeful misinformation.

With the use of blockchain technology, Terciv will create a way to authenticate the origin of news articles and other forms of published content on the web, so that the consumers of that information can have a way to verify the veracity of the information. At our core, Terciv is designed to create a system that will bring about the validation of news articles distributed online.  Terciv uses blockchain technology in a distributed ledger fashion along with machine learning for pattern recognition to properly index articles from confirmed reputable sources into a white list, while blacklisting purposely deceitful articles via the use of pattern recognition algorithms.

description: SwiftGo is a SaaS/HaaS platform, with patented add-on modules, that allows brick-and-mortar retail stores to personalize in-store shopping.

full_description:
SwiftGo is a SaaS/HaaS platform, with patented add-on modules, that allows brick-and-mortar retail stores to personalize in-store shopping. It has developed a platform that allows brick-and-mortar retail stores to eliminate check-out lines and provides its customers with a swift and personalized in-store shopping experience, whilst simultaneously addressing shrinkage. SwiftGo platform comprising of Software as a Service and Hardware as a Service module (for addressing shrinkage concerns) that can be deployed separately but work together seamlessly. SwiftGo was founded in 2017 and is based in Houston, Texas, United States.

full_description:
SDVA Solutions was founded upon the belief that customer service is the most important factor in business. Providing personalized, accurate customer service will not only retain a current customer but also attract new ones. Small business owners wear many hats making sure clients are taken care of, but can they realistically answer every call that comes into the business? What if that one missed call is your most loyal client and because they couldn’t reach you they changed services? Don’t take that chance! They provide phone coverage 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year. Their staff is comprised of tenured agents with a passion for customer service and will represent your business with the professionalism it deserves. Staffing issues? Emergency? Language barriers? No problem. Coverage, both English and Spanish, is always available even when life throws you a curve ball such as a sick employee or natural disaster such as a hurricane.  Think you can’t afford it? Think again! An average, entry level, 40 hour a week receptionist makes roughly $23000 a year plus the cost of hiring, training, insurance, and benefits. Depending on your call volume, their answering service runs about $400-$1000 a month with none of the other fees! 
SDVA Solutions also provides virtual assistance services including scheduling, billing, data entry, print marketing, online chat monitoring, and many more administrative tasks. Helping businesses save money and be more efficient quickly shows positive reactions in their customer’s satisfaction.

full_description:
Roomnett is a shared accommodation and roommate finder website & App where you find a like-minded roommate that you can share a home with. 

It's the trusted community marketplace that provides a cheaper and easy way to rent out your Spare Room or find your ideal Room to rent. Roomnett helps you find the perfect roommate and like-minded people to share a home with.

As a peer-to-peer rental marketplace, Roomnett is making it easy and safer for young people, professionals, expats, millennials, commuters, tenants, and homeowners to search for room rentals, sublets, and roommates. Room owners and renters are easily able to list their place and room needs, then Roomnett automatically verifies every listing and offers additional safety features for the Room owners and renters to connect safely. 

We are building a trusted community marketplace by providing a cheaper and easy way for renters to find accommodation appropriate and flexible enough for their needs in a convenient location. Roomnett cultivates a sharing-economy by allowing homeowners, landlords, and tenants to rent out their spare room or make occupancy arrangements like co-tenancy or sub-tenancy for mid-term to long-term stay.

description: PlayNice is the first platform to legally stop cyberbullying.
headquarters: New York, New York, United States
industry_groups: Apps, Internet Services, Mobile, Platforms, Software
full_description:
PlayNice is the first App to legally stop CyberBullying. Using the same
Confidentiality Agreements that celebrities use, PlayNice allows anyone to access
the tools to keep themselves and people they know, protected from online abuse
and CyberBullying. Send and sign these agreements with people you meet online or
already know, and agree to one limitation on the relationship; never harm each other
online. If the agreement is broken, PlayNice has a suite of tools to enforce the
agreement, help remove the harmful content, and hold the offender accountable.

For years, the celebrities have used confidentiality agreements and NDA’s to keep
their private lives, private. They have been proven to work but the legal fees can cost
a fortune, and generally, they exist in a clunky paper format and are not easy to sign
and maintain. PlayNice makes it easy and accessible for all by allowing people on
the App to easily sign and protect each other, and store the agreements safely on the
App. PlayNice’s goal is for the millennial market to be the first generation to take
control of their online privacy and digital footprint, and not allow people they know
to forever damage their reputation online.

description: PharmID provides accurate verification of the medication and concentration in pharmaceutical products within seconds.

full_description:
PharmID provides accurate verification of the medication and concentration in pharmaceutical products within seconds. It utilizes MarqMetrix patented chemical verification technology to precisely and accurately identify the chemical make-up of medications in the hospital and the non-acute care marketplace. 

MarqMetrix has been providing non-destructive quantitative and qualitative Raman Spectroscopy tools and services to industrial clients (petro- and agri-chemical, pharmaceutical, and others) for the last 5+ years. Two of the founders of PharmID have family connections in pharmacy, so it was only a matter of time before the connection of Raman Spectroscopy to assist pharmacy in identification and verification of medications was made.

PharmID is currently pursuing products to support drug diversion prevention, IV compounding verification, and other activities where knowing for certain what-the-drug-is important.

PharmID was founded in early 2017 to develop and commercialize technology developed by MarqMetrix for healthcare and pharmacy uses.

OneUp works with Facebook, Twitter, Pinterest, Linkedin, and Google+.

description: Software tools that help protect consumers from deceptive or misleading content on the internet.
industries: Artificial Intelligence, Browser Extensions, Content, Machine Learning, News, Predictive Analytics, Productivity Tools, Social News, Software

full_description:
Nobias is a tech startup dedicated to promoting responsible/inclusive technology, countering online manipulation, misinformation and disinformation. Its first product and vision for putting the power of informed media consumption in the hands of users is a Google Chrome extension that shows the bias and credibility of news served up by Google search results and Facebook’s newsfeed. Users can drill down to evaluate individual articles and authors. Giving context about the news, even before users click, can counter the effects of algorithmic curation that may keep them in a filter bubble. And knowing about the credibility can help people avoid fake news. 

The company was founded in 2017 by CEO Tania Ahuja, a dynamic leader who holds a PhD in finance and is an accomplished business professional with extensive knowledge in data mining and risk management. She is building experienced journalism and AI advisory teams, to help keep Nobias effective and on the cutting edge.

description: A comprehensive alternative cash management platform
industries: Big Data, Employee Benefits, Food and Beverage, Mobile, Mobile Payments, Non Profit, Sports, Universities
headquarters: New York, New York, United States
industry_groups: Administrative Services, Data and Analytics, Financial Services, Food and Beverage, Health Care, Mobile, Other, Payments, Software, Sports
full_description:
The managing and disbursement of internal funds within the collegiate athletics, business, and nonprofits markets are outdated and prone to bottle-necking; resulting in a lack of transparency and wasted resources.

We believe that MunchMoney solves this problem of antiquated managing and disbursement of internal funds for these markets, as our company offers a modern cost-efficient solution that bridges the gap by precisely managing these funds for organizations through fully controllable physical & virtual “smart” debit cards designed for unique programs.

MunchMoney cards work like debit cards except they only work within the parameters and balances set by the user (think of MunchMoney as kind of like TV parental controls but for debit cards). Each card is engineered to match the ease and flexibility of cash while also providing insights for greater fiscal efficiencies. Our mission is to revolutionize cash and cash-equivalent spending.

full_description:
Our mission is to use great communication and best-business development practices to enable entrepreneurs and businesses of all sizes and budgets to achieve their dream of having that beautifully designed and state-of-the-art app or website they know they need to succeed in 2017.

We know we live in a crazy, fast-paced age of information. So many people and companies have incredible, inventive ideas or simply need to promote their business online but don't really know how to go about it. Between the plethora of options and misinformation, it's easy to feel lost and overwhelmed. The most frustrating thing faced by business owners and visionaries alike is the lack of dedication by some companies and the incompetence of others. To be more specific, delay in delivery, delay in revisions, turbulent communication, and shoddy code have been the most disturbing experiences for business owners dealing with web design and development companies.

Enter New Old Road Tech. From building revolutionary apps to providing a powerful, easy-to-find online presence, New Old Road is here to make sure your needs are met with professionalism and courtesy. Because we excel at the newest trends and technologies, we are well equipped to make any dream a reality. Our most important goal, however, is to make sure there is in-depth communication from pre-design to launch and beyond. We're not here to turn over countless projects and move on, we're here to cater to our customers and ensure we enjoy a life-long relationship.

description: We are the world’s first Decentralized Blockchain Service Provider (DBSP) bringing blockchain to those "off-chain"
industry_groups: Information Technology, Other, Software
full_description:
MIMIR Blockchain Solutions, based in Atlanta, Georgia, is the world’s first Decentralized Blockchain Service Provider (DBSP), a new industry category that takes Blockchain as a Service (BaaS) beyond the cloud. Our flagship product, the MIMIR Blockchain to Internet (B2i) Bridge, brings blockchain to the “off-chained” by allowing direct access to the Decentralized Application ecosystem from any web connected device without the need for third-party trust; with limited or, in some cases, no pre-installed software necessary.

By leveraging existing nodes, the MIMIR Bridge can help B2B and B2C clients improve economics and smooth capacity issues. This innovative approach will also address current issues with blockchain (namely security, scalability, and accessibility).

The MIMIR B2i Token, the value mechanism behind the MIMIR B2i Bridge solution, will go beyond the cloud and traditional Blockchain as a Service (Baas) offerings. Our token is truly the first of its kind. In exchange for cryptocurrency, users will be given a small amount of MIMIR B2i tokens that will act as its own piece of infrastructure. Thus our B2I tokens, which can be used to actively participate on the network, become a steady source of revenue for holders.
	
While there is potential for penetration of the business to consumer (B2C) market, MIMIR sees business to business (B2B) as a larger market for growth (Frost & Sullivan, estimates best B2B e-commerce is set to reach $6.7 trillion by 2020). MIMIR is actively pursuing case study partners with Dapp developers and web API’S. These markets are in need of infrastructure solutions to satisfy the demand for nodes, which presently out-paces supply by an internal estimates of 48,248%. 

We believe our B2i technology can be seen in many areas of modern business, including but not limited to:

Identity Protection 
Car sharing 
Augmented Reality 
Business Preservation/Expansion
Asset Tracking/Supply Chain (Natural Disaster Relief/Humanitarian Efforts)
Secure Fund Transfer

MIMIR will have a live alpha test beginning early January 2018. Our Token sale will launch in Q1 of 2018. It is our expectation to have multiple case study partners by mid-2018, and an active beta version of the MIMIR B2i product ready for commercialization in late 2018.

Magic AI Corp is not building general purpose AI, but is rather focused on nonverbal forms of data and communication related to humans and animals. description: LienIQ decentralizes residential non-performing second lien analytics-based investing.
headquarters: New York, New York, United States
industry_groups: Financial Services, Information Technology, Real Estate
full_description:
In this late-cycle credit environment, several factors suggest off-the-run, short-duration,
high-yielding assets may be the sweet spot in the credit investment space as these types
of assets may outperform through a much overdue downturn. A firm with the right expertise
in real estate, credit modeling, and application development can position itself to capture this
opportunity.

These factors include, but are not limited to: (1) Low rates and flat yield curves, which indicate that the market may not be
compensating investors for moving out the maturity spectrum. (2) A re-levered consumer base that may not be able to meet their financial obligations
and may therefore change spending behavior. (3) Punitive regulations instituted after the last financial crisis potentially making
originators, mainly banks, less apt to hold distressed assets on balance sheet. (4) A reluctance of traditional managers to engage in smaller, fragmented asset
markets that may be costly to enter.

LienIQ is that firm. We are made up of fixed income and technology professionals that are
committed to capturing unique investment opportunities in the consumer credit space.
By marrying cutting-edge, machine-learning based, financial modeling and traditional real
estate capital structure analysis with the distributed, bottom-up power of blockchain
technology, we can engage the broader investment community and democratize the rewards
from this endeavor.

Our first order of business is purchasing and working out Non-Performing Loans (NPL’s)
in the second lien mortgage space. NPL’s present a unique opportunity because they are
rising in volume, can be sourced effectively through our network, and traditional funds tend to
avoid them because are smaller in size and carry headline risk. Furthermore, they are
buttressed by home prices, which may continue to rise through the next downturn. By
researching the market, the team discovered that a rigorous, model-driven approach was
lacking and that a scale-able second lien portfolio pricing engine may provide smaller
participants a marked advantage. In response to this insight, the team created the first version
of a small-scale, proprietary lien scoring system to evaluate claims.

Our vision is to institute a best-in-class investment process for the consumer credit space
through the next downturn so we may generate dividends for our token-holders. With
improvements of our quanta-mental approach, LienIQ will solidify this competitive
advantage. We already built and used the first version of this model to evaluate ~$5MM in
second lien portfolios and purchase several individual liens. In addition, we developed similar
models for other consumer credit assets, like unsecured term loans used for pricing and
underwriting purposes. By enhancing the model suite with more relevant and timely historical
performance data, additional human capital, and an expanded sourcing network, we may be
able to not only project future cash-flows, but also the borrower order of payments across
many financial obligations. We then may be able to intelligently select, purchase, and workout
those portfolios to monetize this informational advantage and outperform other market
participants.

description: InOrbit is a cloud-based robot management platform to help robotics developers and operators scale their robot fleets.
industries: Artificial Intelligence, Cloud Data Services, Enterprise Software, Robotics, SaaS
industry_groups: Artificial Intelligence, Data and Analytics, Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Science and Engineering, Software
full_description:
InOrbit is bridging the autonomy gap through a cloud robot management platform that enables robotics companies and operators to develop, deploy and orchestrate autonomous robots at global scale. The commercial service robot market, is growing over 40% YoY and is expected to hit $50B by 2024.

InOrbit is pioneering the new field of RobOps, or DevOps for Robotics -- think of it as Splunk/Datadog for Robots. InOrbit’s multi-cloud platform provides secure, real-time analytics and data collection, robot performance monitoring (RPM), incident management and remote interventions. The company’s proprietary technology, including adaptive diagnostics and predictive analytics, is able to derive unique value by leveraging industry-wide data that provides InOrbit’s customer’s insight they are unable to obtain on their own.  InOrbit has access to over 300 Petabytes of data per month and can learn faster than any robotics company by operating across different robots and industry verticals. Customers and partners include Google, Qualcomm, Sprint, Brain Corp., Bossa Nova Robotics and over a dozen other robot manufacturers that range from early stage to scaling. 

InOrbit’s founding team includes Mario Munich, a pioneer in robotics and former SVP Technology at iRobot (through acquisition of Evolution Robotics, where he was CTO); Julian Cerruti, an expert in complex systems, robotics and augmented reality (experience with Willow Garage, creator of de facto standard Robot Operating System, Savioke, Clearpath, Google, IBM); and Florian Pestoni, with experience leading product teams reaching hundreds of millions of users at large-scale cloud companies (formerly at Microsoft, Adobe, Atlassian, Facebook, Ooyala). Together the team holds well over 50 patents in security, autonomous navigation, image processing, distributed systems and collaboration, with diverse experience including starting companies, scaling teams, shipping products at scale and achieving venture-backed exit through acquisition.

description: Easy to use property management software for small-to-mid-sized landlords.
industry_groups: Real Estate, Software
full_description:
Innago offers a cloud-based property management platform for landlords with small to midsize property portfolios. With Innago, users can collect rent, manage leases, collect signatures and manage tenants.

Landlords can collect rent via ACH or credit cards. Users can set rents, configure late fees, waive fees if needed and manage recurring charges like parking fees and utility bills. Email reminders are sent to tenants before rent is due, when rent is due and if a payment is late. Innago also includes invoice generation, late fee assessment, account deposits and invoice tracking. Multiple bank accounts are supported.

Esignature tools let tenants sign leases remotely from mobile or desktop devices. Landlords and tenants can access documents remotely as well, built-in lease templates allow users to configure rental amounts, lease dates and pet addendums. Users can also add, remove, and sublease tenants. Communication tools let users contact individuals or entire properties.

Our mission is to make renting simple, accessible, and affordable for landlords of any size. Innago is 100% free to use and comes with a long list of affordable features.

Do you have subsidiaries, departments, or products utilizing a different set of infrastructures, standardizations, and technologies?

Resource management, legacy systems, API management, silo nightmares, multi-cloud orchestration, IT Ops - all those are huge IT plumbing challenges preventing you from accelerating time-to-market and leaving you with a painful and lengthy journey to build and release applications… 

Unfortunately with all the tools in the market, there isn’t a solution that allows you to write your code and push a button to be up and running. Lots of IT Plumbing is required, and it gets even more complicated after your first release.

Introducing SOAJS Enterprise, a Complete & Adaptive solution to integrate client Environments into Infrastructures by breaking the silos, modernizing & harmonizing existing IT infrastructure, bringing calm to chaos, and automating IT Ops. “Click. Click. Done! It’s that easy.” 

Don’t let standardization and difference in style and technologies slow you down. Unlike others, SOAJS enterprise harmonization is the solution that takes place effortlessly, quickly, and cost effectively.

Integrate and orchestrate multiple source code, applications, infrastructure and technologies in a simplistic and secured approach by forming a modernized distributed service oriented architecture that unleashes speed and empowers any member of the enterprise.

SOAJS™ Enterprise is the solution to eliminate the IT Plumbing pain and unleash speed. 
You can:
Deploy from source code, 
Manage, integrate, and configure resources, 
Orchestrate multi-cloud environments, 
Create multi-tenant and multi-layer secured API, 
Build multi-tenant, multi-version and multi-platform releases in a simplistic approach empowering any member of the enterprise, 
Create custom continuous integration and continuous delivery, per environment, per product, per department, per team, per resource, per technology and per repository
Access to the most complete analytics and metrics dashboard giving you full visibility to make smarter decision in maximizing your operation outcome while minimizing the cost.

Join now and let us show you how SOAJS Enterprise has modernized the IT infrastructure of many organizations and helped them achieve durable digital transformation and bring innovation in-house

description: Gameday allows its users to play fantasy sports on Messenger.
industries: Fantasy Sports, Online Games, Web Apps

full_description:
Gameday allows its users to play fantasy sports on Messenger.

Gameday, a startup part of Y Combinator’s Summer ’17 batch, has made a few tweaks to daily fantasy sports so it can be accessible to everyone.

First, they’re building it into Messenger. This means you don’t have to visit a dedicated site each day and navigate a complicated UI – you just open Messenger and start chatting with their bot, which walks you through entering games and creating lineups.

It’s also totally free to play, which also cuts down on the intimidation factor and makes it fan (and family) friendly. Users can select real prizes like apparel and gift cards that can be bought with in-app currency awarded to contest winners.

And the last difference is that the games offered are simpler and designed to be more fun to play than traditional daily fantasy sports.

description: Gitcoin is a platform that enables open source developers to monetize their work when it is used.
industries: Cryptocurrency, Developer Platform, Ethereum, FinTech, Open Source
industry_groups: Financial Services, Other, Payments, Software
full_description:
Gitcoin is a platform to enable open source developers to monetize their work when it is used.

Gitcoin was borne of the community in Boulder, Colorado's thriving tech scene. One of the most amazing things about the Boulder community is the #givefirst mantra. The founding team has built their careers off of advice, mentorship, and relationships in the local tech community.

Gitcoin is built upon the Ethereum network, and the solidity smart contract programming language. Ethereum provides opportunities to align incentives across actors in the ecosystem. By programming rights of stakeholders directly into smart contracts, actors are incentivized to provide value, and edge cases are handled _without_ having to involve legacy legal enforcement mechanisms.

The founder of Gitcoin, Kevin Owocki, has experience as an organizer of Boulder Startup Week, Ignite Boulder, StartupCTO.io, Boulder Blockchain Meetup, and the open-source projects by trader, adblock-to-bitcoin, YouveGotETH, and ColoradoCoin. The stronger the community is, the more successful open source projects are. The stronger open source projects are, the stronger the community is.

Gitcoin is a project that combines the #givefirst mantra of the Boulder community with capitalistic incentives to write great software. By enabling Repo Maintainers, developers, and financiers to find one another, Gitcoin pushes open-source software forward.

description: Give and Take technology allows employees to collaborate and share knowledge in order to improve engagement, efficiency, and productivity.

Give and Take technology allows employees to collaborate and share knowledge in order to improve engagement, efficiency, and productivity. 

Give and Take takes the concepts of generalized reciprocity and social capital made famous in Wharton professor Adam Grant’s bestselling Give and Take and delivers it to enterprises in an accessible, scalable, measurable platform called Givitas. 

By fostering a giving culture, companies of all sizes drive positive business outcomes like increased employee efficiency, productivity, loyalty, and engagement. Give and Take is headquartered in Ann Arbor, Michigan and online at www.giveandtakeinc.com.

For connected sensor, device, and mobile app makers, our platform provides an end to end solution for adding cloud connectivity and data-driven service revenue streams to those devices that save time and money developing, deploying and operating an IoT product, while also enabling new revenue streams for their device data and context.

For data and analytic-driven service providers, our platform provides an efficient and scalable path to access IoT or connected device data and end customer context for analytics to enable responsive service integration into those devices.

The platform can be deployed in a vertically integrated fashion for customers who want to implement both the devices and the connected services, or it can be leveraged as a multi-sided market connecting device makers, data provider, service providers, and analytic or visualization app developers together both technically and commercially.

The platform is cloud infrastructure agnostic, so customers can choose their preferred cloud infrastructure provider and avoid being locked in, or even deploy in a private data center.

description: ACRES ReServ is a public benefit corporation dedicated to elevating clinical research site quality, safety and productivity
industry_groups: Health Care, Information Technology, Professional Services
full_description:
In 2019, the Alliance for Clinical Research Excellence and Safety (ACRES) and co-founders Greg Koski, Daniel O'Connor and Larry Kennedy created ACRES ReServ (ReServ) as a Delaware Public Benefit Corporation to provide concentrated, focused support for the tremendously successful ACRES Site Accreditation & Standards Initiative (SASI). ACRES in partnership with the British Standards Institution developed the first uniform global standard for clinical research sites and independent third-party accreditation. Accreditation promotes professionalism and enhances sustainability while reducing the cost and time required to effectively evaluate promising products. It also supports regulatory oversight and compliance while ensuring the promotion of responsible ethical conduct to make new, safe medicines available to patients more quickly and with improved outcomes. ACRES ReServ was created to commercialize the accreditation standard worldwide. 

As a public benefit corporation, the ReServ directive serves ACRES mission while harnessing the power of entrepreneurial enterprise to deliver and support innovative clinical research site accreditation, operational and regulatory and compliance solutions. By operating as a for-profit business venture, ReServ’s charter is to promote and enhance the safety, quality and productivity of clinical research worldwide.

description: Blueprint Advisory offers Salesforce consulting, software development, and business advisory services.
industry_groups: Information Technology, Professional Services, Software
full_description:
Blueprint Advisory is a Salesforce product development outsourcer (PDO) and system integrator (SI).

We provide startups, enterprise companies, and global product managers the trusted expertise that can only be learned in the trenches building successful software products from the ground up.

The core leadership team at Blueprint was previously responsible for creating, scaling, and ultimately exiting a company called Talent Rover.  Blueprint's CEO, Brandon Metcalf, founded Talent Rover in 2010, leveraging the Salesforce platform to create a staffing and recruitment software application focused on the sales-to-invoice customer journey.  It quickly grew to eight global offices and went on to become the 9th fastest-growing software company in America (Inc.500) in 2017, before being acquired by Bullhorn in 2018 and becoming an integral part in the company's all-in-one sales and recruitment cloud-based solution.

Through Talent Rover's explosive growth and acclaimed startup journey, a select group of the company's leadership team saw firsthand the wide range of obstacles and challenges software companies face when developing Salesforce solutions and bringing new products to market.  Leveraging nearly a decade of lessons learned building Talent Rover from idea to exit, Blueprint Advisory provides companies of all sizes with the kind of expertise that can only be gained building a world-class global software company.

full_description:

Unfortunately, today the only protection users have from anyone accessing their personal information and assets is their login.

Cyphlens’ patent pending technology protects sensitive information viewed by the user in such a way that even if the user's online bank account is hacked or login credentials are stolen, account information protected by Cyphlens remains inaccessible to the attacker. Cyphlens protects sensitive content in documents, on websites, in emails, across all messaging platforms (e.g., Slack, Telegram, WhatsApp) and more.

description: Predictive analytics leveraging the social determinants of health to identify and monitor chronic disease risk early.
industries: Analytics, Artificial Intelligence, Health Care, Machine Learning, Predictive Analytics
industry_groups: Artificial Intelligence, Data and Analytics, Health Care, Science and Engineering, Software
full_description:
Decode Health offers a proven data analytics solution that can predict and monitor chronic disease early.
Decode’s health management analytics solution leverages a variety of healthcare data sources including proprietary social determinants of health data. Decode can apply this approach across a variety of chronic conditions including: multiple sclerosis, Crohn’s, ulcerative colitis, chronic kidney disease (CKD), COPD, diabetes, and others. Relying on our deep disease knowledge and expert data modeling techniques, the platform finds patients who are trending towards a diagnosis, are about to experience a high-cost adverse event, or are misdiagnosed and being treated with unnecessary, expensive drugs, often biologics.

Our patent-pending technology provides insights that enhance care managers’ ability to optimize the care pathway to reduce disease risk and improve overall outcomes for their patients.

In the face of the COVID-19 pandemic, Decode has applied its approach to predict increased rates of new cases, deaths, and hospitalizations. Decode delivers an early warning system to policymakers and health officials that enables proactive decision-making tied to faster economic recovery and enhanced COVID-19 risk mitigation including a second or third ‘wave’ of infection.

description: GZX is a SaaS platform for the bilateral trading of environmental emission credits.
industries: Biofuel, Biomass Energy, Clean Energy, Energy, Fuel, Oil and Gas, Renewable Energy, SaaS, Software, Trading Platform
industry_groups: Energy, Financial Services, Lending and Investments, Natural Resources, Software, Sustainability
full_description:
GZX® by GZ Energy, LLC is an industry leading custom-built software that eliminates market friction and ushers in a new era of emissions trading for separated (K2) Renewable Identification Numbers (RINs), California Low Carbon Fuel Standard (LCFS) credits, and Oregon Clean Fuels Program (CFP) credits. The platform's advantages and features were designed by a former trader to provide market participants with a modern way in which to efficiently transact compliance credits for physical bilateral settlement off platform.

•	Broker and Frustration Free Trading

description: mltrons enables organizations to leverage & build advanced machine learning algorithms without ever writing a single line of code.
industries: Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Predictive Analytics
headquarters: New York, New York, United States
industry_groups: Artificial Intelligence, Data and Analytics, Science and Engineering, Software
full_description:
In today’s world, data is getting larger and complicated to analyze. Almost every company is gathering a lot of data and is looking for professionals who can analyze that data in order to make predictions & generate insights. Companies like Tencent are employing several thousands of data scientists who are using data and building machine learning models in order to generate predictions & make smarter decisions. Unfortunately, the demand for data scientist exceeds the supply. According to McKinsey research, there will be a shortage of 1.25 million data scientists by 2024. Quality data scientists are hard to find and expensive to employ as a single quality data scientist costs about $117,000 per year according to Glassdoor research. The data scientist has to then spend 45% of their time on model building that we believe is a very repetitive & time consuming process. On top of that, organizations that are thinking about building an in-house solution require more than 3.5 million RMB in investment & usually more than 6 months of development. 

That is why we’re building mltrons, which is predictive analytics in 5 clicks. We’re are enabling organizations to build and leverage advanced machine learning & deep learning algorithms without ever writing a single line of code or worrying about investing in infrastructure. The users just need to prepare the data and upload it into the application after which they need to tell the system what they want to predict. Then automatically, our AI engine builds the best fit model for their problems and provides them with real-time predictions and insights. 

Our AI engine is built on a robust architecture with state of the art algorithms. Our goal is to get companies from raw data to actionable predictions in the fastest way possible. Mltrons Ai engine can be connected to various data sources after which it loads the data, prepares and cleans the data, build hundreds of thousands of combinations of algorithms and then selects the best model for the problem that can be easily deployed in one click, either by using REST API, uploading new data or using our visual prediction. In essence, mltrons is simple yet scalable. But most importantly, mltrons is accurate & intelligent because as more data is fed it, it gets smarter.

Opyn allows users to earn a premium or take views on assets by trading options on ETH and ERC20s.

Opyn v2 offers European, cash-settled options that auto-exercise upon expiry. Opyn options (oTokens) are ERC20s, so they can be trading on any decentralized exchange that follows the ERC20 standard.

Opyn v1 laid the foundation for DeFi options as the first live ERC20 options protocol. For the first time, anyone could create, buy, and sell options on any ERC20 token. Opyn v1 will remain live on the Ethereum network, providing a venue for American, physically settled options. We will continue to launch ERC20 options on Opyn v1.

description: Building connections one conversation at a time.
industries: Consumer, Dating, Lifestyle, Mobile Apps, Social Network
industry_groups: Apps, Community and Lifestyle, Internet Services, Mobile, Other, Software
full_description:
The COVID-19 pandemic brought the world to a halt. Singles found themselves feeling more alone now than ever. Couples, who once stood strong during their greatest challenges, are now crumbling under the weight of the stresses the pandemic has brought. The pandemic forced us all to change how we live our lives and to think about what’s most important: the need and desire for a deeper connection with someone. 

Singles need help connecting during actual dates (because this is where dating apps fail) and couples need help starting conversations beyond work, finances, schedules and kids. So how do you form a connection and maintain it?

For singles looking to form a genuine connection on actual dates and couples looking to maintain their connection, 3rdDegree is the ice-breaking game that facilitates new levels of open communication. It’s a connection building app that takes honesty and vulnerability to create high quality conversations. It encourages face to face communication to build a connection by two people getting to ask the date questions we all want to know. Through game-like quizzes that score you based on your effort to open up, you will find out new, fun tidbits about your person. With questions that foster a deeper connection to help reveal the true essence of a person, singles can see if they truly are a good match beyond surface level and couples are motivated by the delight in unexpected discoveries of one another. 

Dig deeper with 3rdDegree on first dates, following dates, or throughout a lifetime together.

full_description:
PostureHealth is empowering people to be more healthy and productive during the workday and beyond.

We realize that the majority of people's workdays are spent sitting in front of a computer screen, which often leads to habits that produce poor health and productivity outcomes. We are driven by a tireless pursuit to understand how we can seamlessly integrate delightful technology into people's workdays to ultimately create new habits that produce better health and productivity outcomes.

We've started by building an award-winning posture correction software that gently nudges users when they slouch. Leading companies offer PostureHealth to their employees as an ergonomic benefit, we have thousands of end-users, and top investors like Y Combinator. Yet, we still have so much more to do to help people achieve workday bliss.

Whether as an adopter or a member of our team, join us in building a healthier, more productive world.

description: Precog is AI for Data Engineering

Data has become increasingly large and complex, end users have been cutoff, and the data engineer has become paramount. Precog is changing this and giving access and control back to the end users and business teams.

Our solution is a huge leap forward in data transformation and preparation. It’s not just another variation of some open source project, It’s the biggest change in data thinking in 30 years. Our team of world class developers and mathematicians is building technology unlike anything else in the market today. Based on our unique and powerful mathematical foundation, MRA (Multi-dimensional Relational Algebra), our solutions are changing how users gain value from data.

Funded by the best technology investors in the world, and supported by our customers and partners we will continue to push the boundaries of both ease of use and hyper performance for transforming massive complex data sets into ready to use analytic data tables for any application.

description: Let the fun begin with Slap: Sounds like a plan is a new video-based social planning app that supercharges your social life.
industries: Messaging, Mobile Apps, Social Network, Software
headquarters: New York, New York, United States
industry_groups: Apps, Information Technology, Internet Services, Messaging and Telecommunications, Mobile, Software
full_description:
Slap is the new creative way to live your best life with your friends or make new ones. It's for people who don’t like to plan, but are always down to do something fun.

--

We’ve turned the map into a video-based social calendar that captures future plans with our event stories (Video Invite® + Video RSVPs). 

There are plenty of invite services that ‘list’ who’s coming to your event or kickback, but none of them ‘show you’ who’s coming and how excited they are to join in.

It’s not where you are now, it’s where you want to be in the next 24 hours. 


****************
How to use Slap? 
****************

Slap: 

Bored? Record a Slap (Video Invite®) to start an event story telling your friends or the world what you want to do. Then pin the location of where you’ll be on your map.


Explore:

Looking for something to do? Surf the Slap Map to see what your friends have posted they’ll be doing. Don't miss out, spontaneous event stories disappear within the next 24 hours.


Slap back: 

Find something interesting to do? Slap back by recording a video RSVP to tell your friends you’re in. Start enjoying the anticipation of the event as the Slaps start coming in and you see how psyched everyone is.


Messaging: 

Once you Slap back that you'll be joining in, you'll unlock the group chat with everyone else who will be going.

****************


When all of your favorite people are sharing and discovering things for you to join in on, life will get a lot more interesting.

Wingmen was born out of a desire to give a safe, commonsense, and affordable option to our customers to get them and/or their cars to wherever they may need. Our customers deserve to enjoy their lives safely and without regret. We understand that life is more busy than ever before, and every moment is valuable. Prism is a software company operating a centralized, clinical trial meta-data platform. Our technology delivers contextualized trial data and insights. This leads to better trials, better evidence, and more effective decision-making. 

Prism was co-founded in Boston, Massachusetts by Spencer Hey and Brendan Guerin in 2019. Although coming from different worlds—Spencer from academia and Brendan from investing—the two connected after Brendan read Spencer’s STAT News article titled “New insights from a bird's-eye view of clinical trials”. The two quickly bonded over a shared drive to make the world of clinical research more efficient and effective. After countless hours of discussion and white boarding sessions, Prism was born to make this vision a reality.

description: Precog is AI for Data Engineering

full_description:
Data has become increasingly large and complex, end users have been cutoff, and the data engineer has become paramount. Precog is changing this and giving access and control back to the end users and business teams.

Our solution is a huge leap forward in data transformation and preparation. It’s not just another variation of some open source project, It’s the biggest change in data thinking in 30 years. Our team of world class developers and mathematicians is building technology unlike anything else in the market today. Based on our unique and powerful mathematical foundation, MRA (Multi-dimensional Relational Algebra), our solutions are changing how users gain value from data.

Funded by the best technology investors in the world, and supported by our customers and partners we will continue to push the boundaries of both ease of use and hyper performance for transforming massive complex data sets into ready to use analytic data tables for any application.

full_description:
PostureHealth is empowering people to be more healthy and productive during the workday and beyond.

We realize that the majority of people's workdays are spent sitting in front of a computer screen, which often leads to habits that produce poor health and productivity outcomes. We are driven by a tireless pursuit to understand how we can seamlessly integrate delightful technology into people's workdays to ultimately create new habits that produce better health and productivity outcomes.

We've started by building an award-winning posture correction software that gently nudges users when they slouch. Leading companies offer PostureHealth to their employees as an ergonomic benefit, we have thousands of end-users, and top investors like Y Combinator. Yet, we still have so much more to do to help people achieve workday bliss.

Whether as an adopter or a member of our team, join us in building a healthier, more productive world.

description: The first end to end platform for managing infectious disease.
industry_groups: Health Care, Privacy and Security, Software
full_description:
ReturnSafe is helping businesses prevent and contain infectious disease outbreaks by providing Human Resource professionals with a 360-degree view of their workplace and the tools to manage employee health safety.  The HIPAA compliant solution includes daily symptom screening, contact tracing, test data management, vaccination tracking and compliance. Their enterprise-grade platform integrates with Identity Management, HRMS, Building Access Management, Temperature Cameras, and Bluetooth Beacons to provide a holistic system for infectious disease management.

With the push to return to work safely, they have gotten tremendous traction across Education, Manufacturing, Sports & Entertainment, Travel, and Hospitality, and Fortune 1000 businesses - household names like Madonna University, San Antonio Spurs, Simons Foundation, BSE Global, Sesame Street, and The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society.  ReturnSafe was established during the pandemic as a public benefit corporation focused on purpose ahead of profit. The founders are serial entrepreneurs and technologists who are focused on creating a highly usable platform that maintains privacy and security.

description: Let the fun begin with Slap: Sounds like a plan is a new video-based social planning app that supercharges your social life.
industries: Messaging, Mobile Apps, Social Network, Software
headquarters: New York, New York, United States
industry_groups: Apps, Information Technology, Internet Services, Messaging and Telecommunications, Mobile, Software
full_description:
Slap is the new creative way to live your best life with your friends or make new ones. It's for people who don’t like to plan, but are always down to do something fun.

--

We’ve turned the map into a video-based social calendar that captures future plans with our event stories (Video Invite® + Video RSVPs). 

There are plenty of invite services that ‘list’ who’s coming to your event or kickback, but none of them ‘show you’ who’s coming and how excited they are to join in.

It’s not where you are now, it’s where you want to be in the next 24 hours. 


****************
How to use Slap? 
****************

Slap: 

Bored? Record a Slap (Video Invite®) to start an event story telling your friends or the world what you want to do. Then pin the location of where you’ll be on your map.


Explore:

Looking for something to do? Surf the Slap Map to see what your friends have posted they’ll be doing. Don't miss out, spontaneous event stories disappear within the next 24 hours.


Slap back: 

Find something interesting to do? Slap back by recording a video RSVP to tell your friends you’re in. Start enjoying the anticipation of the event as the Slaps start coming in and you see how psyched everyone is.


Messaging: 

Once you Slap back that you'll be joining in, you'll unlock the group chat with everyone else who will be going.

****************


When all of your favorite people are sharing and discovering things for you to join in on, life will get a lot more interesting.

description: StepZen develops APIs and databases dedicated to making it easier for app developers to build user experiences.
industry_groups: Data and Analytics, Software
full_description:
StepZen is a team of API and database nerds dedicated to making it a whole lot easier for app developers to build awesome user experiences. StepZen is on a mission to do for the world of APIs what Google Maps did for directions - reshape it from its current procedural world to a declarative world.

StepZen makes it possible to build user experiences powered by data from multiple and diverse backend data sources without running any infrastructure.

Avoid writing and maintaining complex procedural logic to orchestrate the data you need to power user experiences. Instead, easily build a GraphQL API that enables you to get the data you need with a single query. Whether from databases, APIs, CMSs, or even mock services, StepZen connects and assembles the right data from the right backends.

description: Mobile app that transforms chores into a game that kids absolutely love
industry_groups: Apps, Education, Software
full_description:
Joon is the top family chore tracker that gets kids excited about chores and build positive habits by turning these activities into a fun game. Joon helps parents track chores and allowances while kids complete quests to collect coins and level up their characters. 

In Joon, you assign “Quests” to your kids. When your kids complete their quests, they get coins and experience points that they can use to grow, customize, and care for their virtual companions (Doters). 
Quests can be anything from chores and exercising to learning and completing homework assignments -- the tasks are endless. You can help your children build good habits and discipline by making quests recurring. You can assign and easily track allowances to quests too, turning your standard chore chart into a fun, engaging game that is great for the whole family.

By creating a game around real-life chores and tasks, Joon encourages kids to complete these tasks. This saves parents from nagging and repeatedly asking their kids to do important things like chores, studying, and exercising. Better yet, Joon turns kids into self-starters where they will proactively start doing these types of tasks on their own without parents even having to assign any to them.

full_description:
Envision Bay Consulting, founded in 2021, is headquartered in San Francisco, CA, and focused on marketing and sales for our clients. The specific clientele we represent are industry-leading, multi-billion dollar organizations that have entrusted us with educating consumers
about their products and services. We take our responsibility as liaisons between clients and customers very seriously, abiding by a set of corporate values and beliefs that guide us.

We believe in doing business the right way, one-on-one, and face-to-face, and our state-of-the-art sales training and use of the best CRM software ensures our clients the greatest success in growing their customer base. Our team continues to grow as we focus on their ongoing education and professional development. By offering hands-on management training, we provide a one-of-a-kind opportunity at Envision Bay Consulting that allows entry-level individuals to grow into management within 12-24 months.

We're always looking for energetic and ambitious individuals to help grow our business and manage to set our company apart by placing a significant emphasis on culture and team unity. Be sure to learn more about our company's services, culture, and careers through our website: www.envisionbayconsulting.com!

description: Online platform to connect environmental professionals with companies in need of their services.
industries: Environmental Consulting, Environmental Engineering, Freelance, GreenTech, Internet, Sustainability
industry_groups: Internet Services, Professional Services, Science and Engineering, Sustainability
full_description:
EnviroLinx is an online platform for freelance environmental professionals and customers to connect. Environmental professionals are able to build their profile with past experience, certifications, education, and more. Customers post their job with an RFP for the freelancer to bid and discuss the details. Customers can also search professionals based on their services, experience, and skills. Once selected, the site can facilitate the work through Milestones or the customer and freelancer can work it out on their own.
With the current state we're in, remote and supplemental work is more important than ever. This platform allows you to build or increase your customer base, along with perform remote tasks that were previously not possible.
This concept is similar to the following: TaskRabbit, Thumbtack, HomeAdvisor, Freelancer, UpWork, Rover, etc. - yet specific to environmental services
